
[1]indigo-plant

   IN'DIGO-PLANT, n. A plant of the genus Indigofera, from which is
   prepared indigo. It is a native of Asia, Africa and America, and called
   by the native Americans, anil. The calyx is patent; the carina of the
   corol is furnished with a subulate, patulous spur on each side; the
   legume or pod is linear. Several species are cultivated for making
   indigo, of which the most important are the tinctoria, or common
   indigoplant, the anil, a larger species,and the disperma, which
   furnishes the Guatimala indigo.
